⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Les Propheties
node N1 · N1 · ⟦Les Propheties:N1:432d6c⟧

WHO   — Les Propheties — the riddle-corpus
WHAT  — The most enduring book of prophecy in the Western world — roughly 942 quatrains (Century VII left incomplete), cryptic by design, revered and debunked in equal measure across five centuries.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because their author believed a divine fire could show the shape of things to come; because to speak it plainly was to risk the Inquisition, so it had to be veiled; because a verse obscure enough can never quite be proven wrong, and so can be read by every age that comes.
HOW   — By judicial astrology and the night rite of the brass tripod and the bowl of water; by a verse so allusive — French, Latin, anagram, omen — that it bends to any reader and any century.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the future written in the dark, in riddles — so that I could be read forever, and proven never.

